The Office of the National Cyber Director (ONCD) and the National Space Council recently held a forum to discuss cybersecurity in the space systems ecosystem. The forum aimed to drive action and encourage investments in cybersecurity across the space industry. Government officials and industry participants, including representatives from satellite communications, launch, imagery, cloud and data, defense systems, and venture capital, discussed current cybersecurity practices and strategies to mitigate cyber threats. They emphasized the importance of collaboration between the public and private sectors and the need for comprehensive guidance to improve cybersecurity in space systems. The participants also highlighted the Biden-Harris Administration's National Cybersecurity Strategy, which focuses on building a more resilient and secure digital and space systems ecosystem. Overall, the forum stressed the urgency of addressing cybersecurity challenges in the space industry and emphasized the need for increased investments in cybersecurity.